egory:Male actors in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Punjabi people]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Padma Bhushan in arts]]\n[[Category:People from Ludhiana district]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Hindi film producers]]\n[[Category:Lok Sabha members from Rajasthan]]\n[[Category:Producers who won the Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment National Film Award]]\n[[Category:People of British India]]\n", "name_user": "Bholanathbiswas123", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePersonal life", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dharmendra"}
{"title_page": "Chris Basham", "text_new": "{{short description|English association football player}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Chris Basham\n| image =\n| fullname = Christopher Paul Basham<ref name=\"Statistics\">{{cite web|title=Statistics|url=http://www.premierleague.com/staticFiles/7b/53/0,,12306~152443,00.pdf|publisher=Premier League|accessdate=6 November 2010|format=PDF}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1988|7|20|df=y}}<ref name=Hugman>{{Hugman|22212|accessdate=4 June 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Hebburn]], England\nMarried Joanna Wong \n| height = {{height|ft=5|in=11}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Chris Basham Profile Summary|url=http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/team/player-profile/index.aspx?playerid=359703&tcmuri=99665|publisher=Blackpool F.C.|date=16 July 2012|accessdate=2 January 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130825023822/http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/team/player-profile/index.aspx?playerid=359703&tcmuri=99665|archive-date=25 August 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]], [[midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]]\n| clubnumber = 6\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]]\n| youthyears2 = \n| youthclubs2 = [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]]\n| years1 = 2006\u20132010 | clubs1 = [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]]          | caps1 = 19  | goals1 = 1\n| years2 = 2006\u20132007 | clubs2 = \u2192 [[Stafford Rangers F.C.|Stafford Rangers]] (loan) | caps2 = 3   | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2007\u20132008 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]] (loan)               | caps3 = 13  | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2010\u20132014 | clubs4 = [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]]                        | caps4 = 85  | goals4 = 5\n| years5 = 2014\u2013     | clubs5 = [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]]          | caps5 = 238 | goals5 = 11\n| nationalyears1= \n| nationalteam1= \n| nationalcaps1=  \n| nationalgoals1 =  \n| club-update = 16:56, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n'''Christopher Paul Basham''' (born 20 July 1988) is an English professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]]. He can play in [[Defender (association football)|defence]] or [[midfielder|midfield]].<ref name=\"Basham 1\"/> Having started as a junior with [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]], he played for [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]], as well as having loan spells at [[Stafford Rangers F.C.|Stafford Rangers]] and [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]], prior to joining [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]] in August 2010.\n\n==Career==\n\n===Bolton Wanderers===\nBasham was a member of the youth team at [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] before being released at age sixteen.<ref name=\"Basham 1\"/> Soon after, he joined  [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]], where he signed his first professional contract with the club, signing a two-year deal.<ref name=\"Basham 1\">{{cite news|title=Football League Q&A: Chris Basham on his dream debut, man-marking Frank Lampard and his embarrassing appearance on Soccer AM|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-3969940/Football-League-Q-Basham-dream-debut-man-marking-Frank-Lampard-embarrassing-appearance-Soccer-AM.html|publisher=Daily Mail|date=25 November 2016|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Basham2\"/> In November 2006 Basham joined [[Conference National]] side [[Stafford Rangers F.C.|Stafford Rangers]] on a month's loan, making his debut on 25 November in a 2\u20132 home draw with [[St Albans City F.C.|St Albans City]]. After four appearances for Rangers, Basham returned to Bolton when his loan deal expired.\n\nOn 7 February 2008, Basham joined [[Football League Two|League Two]] side [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]] on loan until the end of the [[2007\u201308 Rochdale A.F.C. season|2007\u201308 season]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Rochdale bring in Bolton's Basham|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/r/rochdale/7233428.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=7 February 2008|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> Making his debut on 12 February 2008 in a 4\u20132 home defeat to [[Hereford United F.C.|Hereford United]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Rochdale 2 - 4 Hereford United|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_3/7236380.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=12 February 2008|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> Baham went on to make a total of 13 appearances for his temporary employers, helping Rochdale to finish fifth in the league and qualify for the [[Football League Two play-offs|League Two play-offs]].\n\nThe [[2008\u201309 Bolton Wanderers F.C. season|following season]] saw Basham make his senior debut for Bolton Wanderers as an 89th-minute substitute in the 4\u20131 win over [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] at the [[Stadium of Light]] on 29 November 2008.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunderland 1 - 4 Bolton Wanderers|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/7742083.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=29 November 2008|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> He scored his first goal on 11 April 2009, in a 4\u20133 defeat to [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] at [[Stamford Bridge (stadium)|Stamford Bridge]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Chelsea 4 - 3 Bolton Wanderers|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/7978838.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=11 April 2009|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> and eventually made a total of eleven appearances that season.\n\nThe [[2009\u201310 Bolton Wanderers F.C. season|following season]] saw Basham making his first appearance came on 29 August 2009, where he came on as a substitute in the second half, in a 3\u20132 loss against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Bolton Wanderers 2 - 3 Liverpool|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/8222679.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=29 August 2009|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> followed up by assisting a winning goal for [[Gary Cahill]], in a 3\u20132 win over [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]] on 12 September 2009.<ref>{{cite news|title=Portsmouth 2 - 3 Bolton Wanderers|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/8245847.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=12 September 2009|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> On 6 November 2009, and after 17 appearances for the club, Basham signed a contract extension with Bolton until the summer of 2012.<ref name=\"sportbox296298\">{{cite web|title=Basham pens Bolton extension|url=http://www.sportbox.tv/football/news/story.php?id=296298|publisher=Sportbox|accessdate=16 August 2010|date=6 November 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724103509/http://www.sportbox.tv/football/news/story.php?id=296298|archivedate=24 July 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref> Remaining on the fringes of the first-team Basham made a total of eight league and two cup appearances in the [[2009\u201310 Bolton Wanderers F.C. season|2009\u201310 season]] before an injury kept him out for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Basham injury adds to Whites woes|url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/5000639.Basham_injury_adds_to_Whites_woes/|publisher=The Bolton News|date=19 February 2010|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Blackpool===\nOn 6 August 2010, Bolton Wanderers turned down a bid from newly promoted Premier League side [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bolton Wanderers reject bid for Basham|url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/8317316.Bolton_Wanderers_reject_bid_for_Basham/|publisher=The Bolton News|date=6 August 2010|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> Eventually, Blackpool made a second bid for Basham, which was accepted by the club<ref>{{cite news|title=Basham still on Seasiders' wanted list|url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/8326084.Basham_still_on_Seasiders____wanted_list/|publisher=The Bolton News|date=12 August 2010|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> and the next day, on 13 August 2010, Basham signed a three-year contract with Blackpool for a fee reported to be in the region of \u00a31million.<ref name=\"blackpool deal\">{{cite web|url=http://www.clicklancashire.com/sport/wigan-athletic-fc/127850-blackpool-fc-closing-in-on-bolton-wanderers-defender-chris-basham.html|title=Blackpool FC closing in on Bolton Wanderers defender Chris Basham|publisher=Click Lancashire|date=13 August 2010|accessdate=18 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708164754/http://www.clicklancashire.com/sport/wigan-athletic-fc/127850-blackpool-fc-closing-in-on-bolton-wanderers-defender-chris-basham.html|archivedate=8 July 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nThe following day after signing for the club, Basham made his debut as a 60th-minute substitute for [[Marlon Harewood]] as Blackpool marked their Premier League debut on the opening day of the [[Blackpool F.C. season 2010\u201311|2010\u201311 season]] with a 4\u20130 win over [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]] at the [[DW Stadium]].<ref name=\"blackpool debut\">{{cite news|last=Sanghera|first=Mandeep|title=Wigan 0-4 Blackpool|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/8904972.stm|accessdate=20 May 2014|website=BBC Sport|date=14 August 2010}}</ref> It wasn't until on 10 November 2010 when he made his second appearance against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]], making his first start and played the whole game, in a 3\u20132 loss.<ref>{{cite news|title=Aston Villa 3 - 2 Blackpool|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_prem/9163006.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=10 November 2010|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> However, Basham spent the most of the season on the reserve, as well as, his own injury concern<ref>{{cite news|title=Basham fights back from leg-break|url=http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sport/football/blackpool-fc/basham-fights-back-from-leg-break-1-3212814|publisher=Blackpool Gazette|date=24 March 2011|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> and at the end of the season, the club were relegated to the Championship.\n\nAfter appearing two matches at the start of the 2011\u201312 season, Basham suffered an injury that kept him out for a month and expected to be loaned out once he returned from injury.<ref>{{cite news|title=Basham seeking action|url=http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sport/football/blackpool-fc/basham-seeking-action-1-3842860|publisher=Blackpool Gazette|date=6 October 2011|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> However, Basham was recalled to the first team once he recovered following the club's injury crisis<ref>{{cite news|title=Problems at the back for Pool|url=http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sport/football/blackpool-fc/problems-at-the-back-for-pool-1-4027951|publisher=Blackpool Gazette|date=2 December 2011|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> and then on 10 December 2011, Basham scored his first goal for Blackpool, heading the first equaliser of a 2\u20132 away draw at [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref name=\"blackpool goal\">{{cite news|title=Southampton 2-2 Blackpool|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/16110443|accessdate=20 May 2014|website=BBC Sport|date=10 December 2011}}</ref> His second goal for the club then came on 21 January 2012, in a 2\u20131 win over [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Blackpool 2 - 1 Crystal Palace|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/16559765.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=21 January 2012|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> Despite missing out for the rest of the season, he made 21 appearance and scoring two times in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2012\u201313 season, Basham appeared in and out of the first team at the start of the season, due to being on the sidelined and played in the reserve.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/bruna-hat-trick-inspires-pool-victory-429403.aspx|title=Bruna Hat-Trick Inspires Pool Victory|publisher=Blackpool F.C.|date=16 October 2012|accessdate=12 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140811191232/http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/bruna-hat-trick-inspires-pool-victory-429403.aspx|archivedate=11 August 2014|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Give me another Basham, please|url=http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sport/football/blackpool-fc/give-me-another-bash-please-1-5218963|publisher=Blackpool Gazette|date=14 December 2012|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> By the time he suffered ankle injury in early-December, he made seven appearance.<ref>{{cite news|title=Blackpool sweat over duo's fitness|url=http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sport/football/blackpool-fc/blackpool-sweat-over-duo-s-fitness-1-5235636|publisher=Blackpool Gazette|date=18 December 2012|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> After returning from injury, Basham then scored his first Blackpool on 29 December 2012, in a 4\u20132 loss against [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Middlesbrough 4 - 2 Blackpool|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/20823204|website=BBC Sport|date=29 December 2012|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> As the 2012\u201313 season progressed, Basham remained in the first team despite suffering from injuries during a match against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] that kept him out for a month<ref>{{cite news|title=Pool midfielder injury shock|url=http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sport/football/blackpool-fc/pool-midfielder-injury-shock-1-5459816|publisher=Blackpool Gazette|date=1 March 2013|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> and went on to finish the 2012\u201313 season, making 28 appearance and scoring once in all competitions. Following this, Blackpool opted to take up their option of a contract extension, keeping Basham under contract until summer 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Thomas Ince & Matt Phillips: Blackpool take up one-year options|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/22465800|website=BBC Sport|date=9 May 2013|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2013\u201314 season, Basham began to establish himself in the first team and started well, helping the club go unbeaten for the first six matches to the start of the season, including scoring his first goal of the season, in a 1\u20131 draw against Middlesbrough on 17 August 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Middlesbrough 1 - 1 Blackpool|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/23644564|website=BBC Sport|date=17 August 2013|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> After appearing four matches throughout September, including scoring another against Leicester City,<ref>{{cite news|title=Blackpool 2 - 2 Leicester City|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24089894|website=BBC Sport|date=21 September 2013|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> Basham's performance earned him Wonga.com Player of the Month award for September.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/basham-collects-september-award-1091455.aspx|title=Basham Collects September Award|publisher=Blackpool F.C.|date=2 October 2013|accessdate=12 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161212220336/http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/basham-collects-september-award-1091455.aspx|archivedate=12 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Despite missing out on two occasions, due to injury<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/forest-preview-2013-1149072.aspx|title=Nottingham Forest Preview|publisher=Blackpool F.C.|date=1 November 2013|accessdate=12 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161212220830/http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/forest-preview-2013-1149072.aspx|archivedate=12 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> and suspension,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/big-preview-sheff-wed-1114-1266382.aspx|title=Big Preview: Sheffield Wednesday|publisher=Blackpool F.C.|date=31 December 2013|accessdate=12 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161212221101/http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/big-preview-sheff-wed-1114-1266382.aspx|archivedate=12 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Basham continued to be in the first team throughout the season and went on to make 42 appearances in all competitions.\n\nAt the end of the 2013\u201314 season, Basham was offered a new contract by the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/retained-list-201314-1554900.aspx|title=Retained List|publisher=Blackpool F.C.|date=16 May 2014|accessdate=12 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140519032844/http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/retained-list-201314-1554900.aspx|archivedate=19 May 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Sheffield United===\nOn 5 June 2014, Basham signed a three-year deal with [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] on a free transfer after his contract with Blackpool came to an end.<ref name=blades>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: Butler and Basham become Blades|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/sheff-utd/sheffield-united-butler-and-basham-become-blades-1-6656651|accessdate=30 June 2014|publisher=Sheffield Star|date=5 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031063750/http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/sheff-utd/sheffield-united-butler-and-basham-become-blades-1-6656651|archive-date=31 October 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> Upon joining the club, Basham was given number six shirt for the new season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/20140801-squad-numbers-1798205.aspx|title=Squad numbers|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=1 August 2014|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214191245/http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/20140801-squad-numbers-1798205.aspx|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBasham made his Sheffield United, making his first start and played 86 minutes before being substituted, in a 2\u20131 loss against [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]] in the opening game of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sky Bet League One: Bristol City edge out Sheffield United at Bramall Lane|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/sheff-utd-vs-bristol-c/314328|publisher=Sky Sports|date=12 August 2014|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Since making his debut, Basham became a first team regular at the club and was praised by Manager [[Nigel Clough]],<ref name=\"BashamSUFC\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/20141023-praise-for-basham-2036068.aspx|title=Praise for Basham|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=23 October 2014|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214191745/http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/20141023-praise-for-basham-2036068.aspx|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> playing most of the season in midfield or centre-back positions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/20141119-chris-basham-bp-2091408.aspx|title=Chris Basham on role|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=19 November 2014|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214192301/http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/20141119-chris-basham-bp-2091408.aspx|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> However, as the 2014\u201315 season progressed, he continued to be in the first team despite facing suspension<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-nigel-clough-chris-basham-2172194.aspx|title=Blades will cope without Basham|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=29 November 2014|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214192638/http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-nigel-clough-chris-basham-2172194.aspx|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-nigel-clough-2329701.aspx|title=Boss on defensive options|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=12 March 2015|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214192844/http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-nigel-clough-2329701.aspx|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> and injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/fixtures-results/match-report/?matchid=3789941&tcmuri=2088459|title=Blades 1-1 Chesterfield - report|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=3 May 2015|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214193148/http://www.sufc.co.uk/fixtures-results/match-report/?matchid=3789941&tcmuri=2088459|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> In the play-offs, Basham played both legs against [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]] and scored in the second leg, in a 5\u20135 draw but unsuccessful,<ref>{{cite news|title=Swindon Town 5-5 Sheffield United (7-6 agg)|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32579316|website=BBC Sport|date=11 May 2015|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> having previously lost 2\u20131 against them in the first leg.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United 1-2 Swindon: Nathan Byrne's late strike hands Robins advantage|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/sheff-utd-vs-swindon/336760|publisher=Sky Sports|date=8 May 2015|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Despite this, he finished his first season, making 50 appearances (20 league) in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2015\u201316 season, Basham continued to be in the first team regular at the club following the arrival of Manager [[Nigel Adkins]] and then played his first match as captain against [[Doncaster Rovers F.C.|Doncaster Rovers]] on 26 September 2015, scoring his first goal of the season, in a 3\u20131 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United 3 - 1 Doncaster Rovers|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34299158|website=BBC Sport|date=26 September 2015|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Throughout the 2015\u201316 season, Basham went on to captain on five occasions following [[Jay McEveley]]'s absence.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-chris-basham-2722299.aspx|title=Captain Bash|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=2 October 2015|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214194721/http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-chris-basham-2722299.aspx|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Basham's second goal of the season came on 28 November 2015, in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Barnsley 1-1 Sheffield United: Late strike from Tykes blunts Blades|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/barnsley-vs-sheff-utd/340311|website=BBC Sport|date=28 November 2015|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Basham also scored two more goals later in the season against [[Colchester United F.C.|Colchester United]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Colchester United 1-2 Sheffield United|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/35269977|website=BBC Sport|date=16 January 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> and [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United 2-0 Walsall: Blade dent Saddlers' promotion hopes|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/sheff-utd-vs-walsall/340560|publisher=Sky Sports|date=2 April 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Despite missing out two league matches, due to injuries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-nigel-adkins-2924652.aspx|title=Trio expected to return|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=29 January 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214200413/http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-nigel-adkins-2924652.aspx|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Blades boss reveals his trust in latest starlet Ben Whiteman|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/blades-boss-reveals-his-trust-in-latest-starlet-ben-whiteman-1-7795822|publisher=The Star|date=15 March 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> and Basham made 49 (44 league) appearances and scoring four times in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2016\u201317 season, Basham continued to be in the first team regular at the club following the arrival of Manager [[Chris Wilder]] and played in the midfield position.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: Louis Reed hopes for more of a chance under Blades boss Chris Wilder|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-chris-wilder-on-the-lessons-of-non-league-1-8155595|publisher=The Star|date=11 September 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Basham then scored his first goal of the season, but was later sent-off in the second half, in a 2\u20132 draw against [[Scunthorpe United F.C.|Scunthorpe United]] on 24 September 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Scunthorpe United 2 \u2013 2 Sheffield United|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37392621|website=BBC Sport|date=24 September 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> After serving a three match suspension,<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: Chris Basham will not face internal investigation after being sent-off at Scunthorpe United|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-chris-basham-will-not-face-internal-investigation-after-being-sent-off-at-scunthorpe-1-8147631|publisher=The Star|date=27 September 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Basham returned to the first team, on 18 October 2016, making his first start from suspension, in a 3\u20130 win against [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Billy Sharp doubles-up to tame Shrews - Shrewsbury Town 0 Sheffield United|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/billy-sharp-doubles-up-to-tame-shrews-shrewsbury-town-0-sheffield-united-3-1-8188320|publisher=The Star|date=18 October 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> followed up by scoring in the next game, in a 3\u20133 draw against [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bradford City 3 - 3 Sheffield United|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37663456|website=BBC Sport|date=22 October 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Two weeks later, on 6 November 2016, Basham scored and set up one of the goals, in a 6\u20130 win over [[Leyton Orient F.C.|Leyton Orient]] in the first round of the FA Cup.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United 6 - 0 Leyton Orient|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37813896|website=BBC Sport|date=6 November 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Due to his impressive performance at the club, Manager Wilder hinted that Basham could be earning a new contract, with a year to his contract left.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: Blades stars are set for new deals|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-blades-stars-are-set-for-new-deals-1-8288244|publisher=The Star|date=14 December 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> As the 2016\u201317 season progressed, Basham began to play in the defense, as a centre-back, partnering with either [[Jack O'Connell (footballer)|Jack O'Connell]], [[Ethan Ebanks-Landell]] and [[Jake Wright]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: Leon Clarke out for a month with ankle injury|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-leon-clarke-out-for-a-month-with-ankle-injury-1-8145720|publisher=The Star|date=25 November 2016|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: Former Bolton star Chris Basham wants to prove nice guys can finish first|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-former-bolton-star-chris-basham-wants-to-prove-nice-guys-can-finish-first-1-8406140|publisher=The Star|date=24 February 2017|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref> Around the same time, Basham played in the midfield position, with [[Paul Coutts]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: John Fleck set to receive the go-ahead|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-john-fleck-set-to-receive-the-go-ahead-1-8185903|publisher=The Star|date=18 October 2016|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref> Then, in a 3\u20130 win over [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] on 14 April 2017, Basham produced an impressive display when he set up two goals.<ref>{{cite news|title=Match Report: Port Vale 0, Sheffield United 3|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/match-report-port-vale-0-sheffield-united-3-1-8494299|publisher=The Star|date=14 April 2017|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref> At the end of the 2016\u201317 season, which saw Sheffield United promoted to [[EFL Championship|Championship]] after six seasons in League One, Basham went on to make 48 appearances and scoring two times in all competitions.\n\nIn July 2017, Basham penned a new two-year contract with the Blades having played a key role in United's title winning promotion from League One.<ref>{{cite news|title=New Contracts|url=https://www.sufc.co.uk/news/2017/july/new-contracts/|publisher=Sheffield United FC|date=18 July 2017|accessdate=18 July 2017}}</ref> On 28 April 2019, Basham saw his second promotion in three seasons with United as the Blades were promoted to the [[Premier League]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48026965|title=Sheffield United promoted to Premier League after Leeds draw|website=BBC Sport|date=2019-04-28|access-date=2019-04-30}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBorn in [[Hebburn]],<ref name=Hugman/> Basham studied at [[Gateshead College]] and trained with their [[Gateshead International Stadium|Academy for Sport]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Basham loving life in the first team|url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/4039542.Basham_loving_life_in_the_first_team/|publisher=The Bolton News|date=12 January 2009|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> He grew up supporting [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]].<ref name=\"sunderland support\">{{cite web|url=http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sport/blackpool-fc/sunderland-fan-can-t-wait-for-crack-at-newcastle-1-5896590|title=Sunderland fan can't wait for crack at Newcastle|publisher=Blackpool Gazette|date=28 July 2013|accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> Basham considers [[Alan Cork]] as a great influence and is indebted to Cork for guiding him throughout his professional football career.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: Why Chris Basham owes a debt of gratitude to Alan Cork|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-why-chris-basham-owes-a-debt-of-gratitude-to-alan-cork-1-8269531|publisher=The Star|date=2 December 2016|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nHaving two years away from football, after leaving Newcastle United at sixteen, Basham worked at [[McDonald's]].<ref name=\"Basham2\">{{cite news|title=Basham goes from Big Mac to big break|url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/3850102.Basham_goes_from_Big_Mac_to_big_break/|publisher=The Bolton News|date=15 November 2008|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> In late 2014, Basham became a father.<ref name=\"BashamSUFC\"/>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|06 May 2019}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n! colspan=\"3\" |League\n! colspan=\"2\" |FA Cup\n! colspan=\"2\" |League Cup\n! colspan=\"2\" |Other\n! colspan=\"2\" |Total\n|-\n!Division||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals\n|-\n|[[Stafford Rangers F.C.|Stafford Rangers]] (loan)\n|[[2006\u201307 Football Conference|2006\u201307]]<ref name=\"0607stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2006|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|[[Conference National]]\n|3||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||4||0\n|-\n|[[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]] (loan)\n|[[2007\u201308 Rochdale A.F.C. season|2007\u201308]]<ref name=\"0708stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2007|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|[[Football League Two|League Two]]\n|13||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||13||0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]]\n|[[2008\u201309 Bolton Wanderers F.C. season|2008\u201309]]<ref name=\"0809stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2008|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Premier League]]\n|11||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||11||1\n|-\n|[[2009\u201310 Bolton Wanderers F.C. season|2009\u201310]]<ref name=\"0910stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2009|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|8||0||1||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||10||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!19||1||1||0||1||0|| colspan=\"2\" |'''\u2014'''||21||1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]]\n|[[2010\u201311 Blackpool F.C. season|2010\u201311]]<ref name=\"1011stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2010|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|2||0||0||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||3||0\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Blackpool F.C. season|2011\u201312]]<ref name=\"1112stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2011|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Football League Championship|Championship]]\n|17||2||3||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||21||2\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Blackpool F.C. season|2012\u201313]]<ref name=\"1213stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2012|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|26||1||2||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||28||1\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Blackpool F.C. season|2013\u201314]]<ref name=\"1314stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2013|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|40||2||1||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||42||2\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!85||5||6||0||3||0|| colspan=\"2\" |'''\u2014'''||94||5\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]]\n|[[2014\u201315 Sheffield United F.C. season|2014\u201315]]<ref name=\"1415stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2014|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Football League One|League One]]\n|37||0||5||0||4||0||4{{efn|2 appearances in [[Football League Trophy]], 2 appearances and 1 goal in [[EFL League One play-offs]]}}||1||50||1\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Sheffield United F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=\"1516stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2015|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|44||3||3||0||1||0||1{{efn|name=FLT|Appearances in [[Football League Trophy]]}}||0||49||3\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Sheffield United F.C. season|2016\u201317]]<ref name=\"1617stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2016|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=23 January 2019}}</ref>\n|43||2||2||1||1||0||2{{efn|name=FLT}}||0||48||3\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Sheffield United F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=\"1718stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2017|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=23 January 2019}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Championship\n|45||2||3||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||50||2\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Sheffield United F.C. season|2018\u201319]]<ref name=\"1819stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2018|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=23 January 2019}}</ref>\n|41||4||1||0||1||0|| colspan=\"2\" |\u2014||43||4\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!210||11||14||1||9||0||7||1||240||13\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!330||17||22||1||13||0||7||1||372||19\n|}\n\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Sheffield United'''\n*[[EFL League One]]: [[2016\u201317 EFL League One|2016\u201317]]<ref>{{cite book |editor-first=John |editor-last=Anderson |title=Sky Sports Football Yearbook 2017\u20132018 |year=2017 |publisher=Headline Publishing Group |location=London |isbn=978-1-4722-3397-4 |pages=326\u2013327}}</ref>\n*[[EFL Championship]] runner-up: [[2018\u201319 EFL Championship|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite book |editor-first=John |editor-last=Anderson |title=Football Yearbook 2019\u20132020 |year=2019 |publisher=Headline Publishing Group |location=London |isbn=978-1-4722-6111-3 |pages=320\u2013231}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100818083649/http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/page/ProfilesDetail/0%2C%2C10432~37982%2C00.html Chris Basham profile] at blackpoolfc.co.uk\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{Sheffield United F.C. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Basham, Chris}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:People from Hebburn]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Bolton Wanderers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Stafford Rangers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Rochdale A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Blackpool F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Sheffield United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|English association football player}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Chris Basham\n| image =\n| fullname = Christopher Paul Basham<ref name=\"Statistics\">{{cite web|title=Statistics|url=http://www.premierleague.com/staticFiles/7b/53/0,,12306~152443,00.pdf|publisher=Premier League|accessdate=6 November 2010|format=PDF}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1988|7|20|df=y}}<ref name=Hugman>{{Hugman|22212|accessdate=4 June 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Hebburn]], England\n| height = {{height|ft=5|in=11}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Chris Basham Profile Summary|url=http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/team/player-profile/index.aspx?playerid=359703&tcmuri=99665|publisher=Blackpool F.C.|date=16 July 2012|accessdate=2 January 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130825023822/http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/team/player-profile/index.aspx?playerid=359703&tcmuri=99665|archive-date=25 August 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]], [[midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]]\n| clubnumber = 6\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]]\n| youthyears2 = \n| youthclubs2 = [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]]\n| years1 = 2006\u20132010 | clubs1 = [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]]          | caps1 = 19  | goals1 = 1\n| years2 = 2006\u20132007 | clubs2 = \u2192 [[Stafford Rangers F.C.|Stafford Rangers]] (loan) | caps2 = 3   | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2007\u20132008 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]] (loan)               | caps3 = 13  | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2010\u20132014 | clubs4 = [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]]                        | caps4 = 85  | goals4 = 5\n| years5 = 2014\u2013     | clubs5 = [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]]          | caps5 = 238 | goals5 = 11\n| nationalyears1= \n| nationalteam1= \n| nationalcaps1=  \n| nationalgoals1 =  \n| club-update = 16:56, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n'''Christopher Paul Basham''' (born 20 July 1988) is an English professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]]. He can play in [[Defender (association football)|defence]] or [[midfielder|midfield]].<ref name=\"Basham 1\"/> Having started as a junior with [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]], he played for [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]], as well as having loan spells at [[Stafford Rangers F.C.|Stafford Rangers]] and [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]], prior to joining [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]] in August 2010.\n\n==Career==\n\n===Bolton Wanderers===\nBasham was a member of the youth team at [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] before being released at age sixteen.<ref name=\"Basham 1\"/> Soon after, he joined  [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]], where he signed his first professional contract with the club, signing a two-year deal.<ref name=\"Basham 1\">{{cite news|title=Football League Q&A: Chris Basham on his dream debut, man-marking Frank Lampard and his embarrassing appearance on Soccer AM|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-3969940/Football-League-Q-Basham-dream-debut-man-marking-Frank-Lampard-embarrassing-appearance-Soccer-AM.html|publisher=Daily Mail|date=25 November 2016|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Basham2\"/> In November 2006 Basham joined [[Conference National]] side [[Stafford Rangers F.C.|Stafford Rangers]] on a month's loan, making his debut on 25 November in a 2\u20132 home draw with [[St Albans City F.C.|St Albans City]]. After four appearances for Rangers, Basham returned to Bolton when his loan deal expired.\n\nOn 7 February 2008, Basham joined [[Football League Two|League Two]] side [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]] on loan until the end of the [[2007\u201308 Rochdale A.F.C. season|2007\u201308 season]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Rochdale bring in Bolton's Basham|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/r/rochdale/7233428.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=7 February 2008|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> Making his debut on 12 February 2008 in a 4\u20132 home defeat to [[Hereford United F.C.|Hereford United]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Rochdale 2 - 4 Hereford United|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_3/7236380.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=12 February 2008|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> Baham went on to make a total of 13 appearances for his temporary employers, helping Rochdale to finish fifth in the league and qualify for the [[Football League Two play-offs|League Two play-offs]].\n\nThe [[2008\u201309 Bolton Wanderers F.C. season|following season]] saw Basham make his senior debut for Bolton Wanderers as an 89th-minute substitute in the 4\u20131 win over [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] at the [[Stadium of Light]] on 29 November 2008.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunderland 1 - 4 Bolton Wanderers|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/7742083.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=29 November 2008|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> He scored his first goal on 11 April 2009, in a 4\u20133 defeat to [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] at [[Stamford Bridge (stadium)|Stamford Bridge]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Chelsea 4 - 3 Bolton Wanderers|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/7978838.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=11 April 2009|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> and eventually made a total of eleven appearances that season.\n\nThe [[2009\u201310 Bolton Wanderers F.C. season|following season]] saw Basham making his first appearance came on 29 August 2009, where he came on as a substitute in the second half, in a 3\u20132 loss against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Bolton Wanderers 2 - 3 Liverpool|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/8222679.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=29 August 2009|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> followed up by assisting a winning goal for [[Gary Cahill]], in a 3\u20132 win over [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]] on 12 September 2009.<ref>{{cite news|title=Portsmouth 2 - 3 Bolton Wanderers|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/8245847.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=12 September 2009|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> On 6 November 2009, and after 17 appearances for the club, Basham signed a contract extension with Bolton until the summer of 2012.<ref name=\"sportbox296298\">{{cite web|title=Basham pens Bolton extension|url=http://www.sportbox.tv/football/news/story.php?id=296298|publisher=Sportbox|accessdate=16 August 2010|date=6 November 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724103509/http://www.sportbox.tv/football/news/story.php?id=296298|archivedate=24 July 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref> Remaining on the fringes of the first-team Basham made a total of eight league and two cup appearances in the [[2009\u201310 Bolton Wanderers F.C. season|2009\u201310 season]] before an injury kept him out for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Basham injury adds to Whites woes|url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/5000639.Basham_injury_adds_to_Whites_woes/|publisher=The Bolton News|date=19 February 2010|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Blackpool===\nOn 6 August 2010, Bolton Wanderers turned down a bid from newly promoted Premier League side [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bolton Wanderers reject bid for Basham|url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/8317316.Bolton_Wanderers_reject_bid_for_Basham/|publisher=The Bolton News|date=6 August 2010|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> Eventually, Blackpool made a second bid for Basham, which was accepted by the club<ref>{{cite news|title=Basham still on Seasiders' wanted list|url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/8326084.Basham_still_on_Seasiders____wanted_list/|publisher=The Bolton News|date=12 August 2010|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> and the next day, on 13 August 2010, Basham signed a three-year contract with Blackpool for a fee reported to be in the region of \u00a31million.<ref name=\"blackpool deal\">{{cite web|url=http://www.clicklancashire.com/sport/wigan-athletic-fc/127850-blackpool-fc-closing-in-on-bolton-wanderers-defender-chris-basham.html|title=Blackpool FC closing in on Bolton Wanderers defender Chris Basham|publisher=Click Lancashire|date=13 August 2010|accessdate=18 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708164754/http://www.clicklancashire.com/sport/wigan-athletic-fc/127850-blackpool-fc-closing-in-on-bolton-wanderers-defender-chris-basham.html|archivedate=8 July 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nThe following day after signing for the club, Basham made his debut as a 60th-minute substitute for [[Marlon Harewood]] as Blackpool marked their Premier League debut on the opening day of the [[Blackpool F.C. season 2010\u201311|2010\u201311 season]] with a 4\u20130 win over [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]] at the [[DW Stadium]].<ref name=\"blackpool debut\">{{cite news|last=Sanghera|first=Mandeep|title=Wigan 0-4 Blackpool|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/8904972.stm|accessdate=20 May 2014|website=BBC Sport|date=14 August 2010}}</ref> It wasn't until on 10 November 2010 when he made his second appearance against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]], making his first start and played the whole game, in a 3\u20132 loss.<ref>{{cite news|title=Aston Villa 3 - 2 Blackpool|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_prem/9163006.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=10 November 2010|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> However, Basham spent the most of the season on the reserve, as well as, his own injury concern<ref>{{cite news|title=Basham fights back from leg-break|url=http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sport/football/blackpool-fc/basham-fights-back-from-leg-break-1-3212814|publisher=Blackpool Gazette|date=24 March 2011|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> and at the end of the season, the club were relegated to the Championship.\n\nAfter appearing two matches at the start of the 2011\u201312 season, Basham suffered an injury that kept him out for a month and expected to be loaned out once he returned from injury.<ref>{{cite news|title=Basham seeking action|url=http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sport/football/blackpool-fc/basham-seeking-action-1-3842860|publisher=Blackpool Gazette|date=6 October 2011|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> However, Basham was recalled to the first team once he recovered following the club's injury crisis<ref>{{cite news|title=Problems at the back for Pool|url=http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sport/football/blackpool-fc/problems-at-the-back-for-pool-1-4027951|publisher=Blackpool Gazette|date=2 December 2011|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> and then on 10 December 2011, Basham scored his first goal for Blackpool, heading the first equaliser of a 2\u20132 away draw at [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref name=\"blackpool goal\">{{cite news|title=Southampton 2-2 Blackpool|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/16110443|accessdate=20 May 2014|website=BBC Sport|date=10 December 2011}}</ref> His second goal for the club then came on 21 January 2012, in a 2\u20131 win over [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Blackpool 2 - 1 Crystal Palace|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/16559765.stm|website=BBC Sport|date=21 January 2012|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> Despite missing out for the rest of the season, he made 21 appearance and scoring two times in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2012\u201313 season, Basham appeared in and out of the first team at the start of the season, due to being on the sidelined and played in the reserve.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/bruna-hat-trick-inspires-pool-victory-429403.aspx|title=Bruna Hat-Trick Inspires Pool Victory|publisher=Blackpool F.C.|date=16 October 2012|accessdate=12 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140811191232/http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/bruna-hat-trick-inspires-pool-victory-429403.aspx|archivedate=11 August 2014|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Give me another Basham, please|url=http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sport/football/blackpool-fc/give-me-another-bash-please-1-5218963|publisher=Blackpool Gazette|date=14 December 2012|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> By the time he suffered ankle injury in early-December, he made seven appearance.<ref>{{cite news|title=Blackpool sweat over duo's fitness|url=http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sport/football/blackpool-fc/blackpool-sweat-over-duo-s-fitness-1-5235636|publisher=Blackpool Gazette|date=18 December 2012|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> After returning from injury, Basham then scored his first Blackpool on 29 December 2012, in a 4\u20132 loss against [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Middlesbrough 4 - 2 Blackpool|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/20823204|website=BBC Sport|date=29 December 2012|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> As the 2012\u201313 season progressed, Basham remained in the first team despite suffering from injuries during a match against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] that kept him out for a month<ref>{{cite news|title=Pool midfielder injury shock|url=http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sport/football/blackpool-fc/pool-midfielder-injury-shock-1-5459816|publisher=Blackpool Gazette|date=1 March 2013|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> and went on to finish the 2012\u201313 season, making 28 appearance and scoring once in all competitions. Following this, Blackpool opted to take up their option of a contract extension, keeping Basham under contract until summer 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Thomas Ince & Matt Phillips: Blackpool take up one-year options|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/22465800|website=BBC Sport|date=9 May 2013|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2013\u201314 season, Basham began to establish himself in the first team and started well, helping the club go unbeaten for the first six matches to the start of the season, including scoring his first goal of the season, in a 1\u20131 draw against Middlesbrough on 17 August 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Middlesbrough 1 - 1 Blackpool|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/23644564|website=BBC Sport|date=17 August 2013|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> After appearing four matches throughout September, including scoring another against Leicester City,<ref>{{cite news|title=Blackpool 2 - 2 Leicester City|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24089894|website=BBC Sport|date=21 September 2013|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> Basham's performance earned him Wonga.com Player of the Month award for September.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/basham-collects-september-award-1091455.aspx|title=Basham Collects September Award|publisher=Blackpool F.C.|date=2 October 2013|accessdate=12 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161212220336/http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/basham-collects-september-award-1091455.aspx|archivedate=12 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Despite missing out on two occasions, due to injury<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/forest-preview-2013-1149072.aspx|title=Nottingham Forest Preview|publisher=Blackpool F.C.|date=1 November 2013|accessdate=12 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161212220830/http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/forest-preview-2013-1149072.aspx|archivedate=12 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> and suspension,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/big-preview-sheff-wed-1114-1266382.aspx|title=Big Preview: Sheffield Wednesday|publisher=Blackpool F.C.|date=31 December 2013|accessdate=12 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161212221101/http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/big-preview-sheff-wed-1114-1266382.aspx|archivedate=12 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Basham continued to be in the first team throughout the season and went on to make 42 appearances in all competitions.\n\nAt the end of the 2013\u201314 season, Basham was offered a new contract by the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/retained-list-201314-1554900.aspx|title=Retained List|publisher=Blackpool F.C.|date=16 May 2014|accessdate=12 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140519032844/http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/retained-list-201314-1554900.aspx|archivedate=19 May 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Sheffield United===\nOn 5 June 2014, Basham signed a three-year deal with [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] on a free transfer after his contract with Blackpool came to an end.<ref name=blades>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: Butler and Basham become Blades|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/sheff-utd/sheffield-united-butler-and-basham-become-blades-1-6656651|accessdate=30 June 2014|publisher=Sheffield Star|date=5 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031063750/http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/sheff-utd/sheffield-united-butler-and-basham-become-blades-1-6656651|archive-date=31 October 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> Upon joining the club, Basham was given number six shirt for the new season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/20140801-squad-numbers-1798205.aspx|title=Squad numbers|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=1 August 2014|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214191245/http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/20140801-squad-numbers-1798205.aspx|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBasham made his Sheffield United, making his first start and played 86 minutes before being substituted, in a 2\u20131 loss against [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]] in the opening game of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sky Bet League One: Bristol City edge out Sheffield United at Bramall Lane|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/sheff-utd-vs-bristol-c/314328|publisher=Sky Sports|date=12 August 2014|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Since making his debut, Basham became a first team regular at the club and was praised by Manager [[Nigel Clough]],<ref name=\"BashamSUFC\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/20141023-praise-for-basham-2036068.aspx|title=Praise for Basham|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=23 October 2014|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214191745/http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/20141023-praise-for-basham-2036068.aspx|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> playing most of the season in midfield or centre-back positions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/20141119-chris-basham-bp-2091408.aspx|title=Chris Basham on role|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=19 November 2014|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214192301/http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/20141119-chris-basham-bp-2091408.aspx|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> However, as the 2014\u201315 season progressed, he continued to be in the first team despite facing suspension<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-nigel-clough-chris-basham-2172194.aspx|title=Blades will cope without Basham|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=29 November 2014|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214192638/http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-nigel-clough-chris-basham-2172194.aspx|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-nigel-clough-2329701.aspx|title=Boss on defensive options|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=12 March 2015|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214192844/http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-nigel-clough-2329701.aspx|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> and injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/fixtures-results/match-report/?matchid=3789941&tcmuri=2088459|title=Blades 1-1 Chesterfield - report|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=3 May 2015|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214193148/http://www.sufc.co.uk/fixtures-results/match-report/?matchid=3789941&tcmuri=2088459|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> In the play-offs, Basham played both legs against [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]] and scored in the second leg, in a 5\u20135 draw but unsuccessful,<ref>{{cite news|title=Swindon Town 5-5 Sheffield United (7-6 agg)|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32579316|website=BBC Sport|date=11 May 2015|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> having previously lost 2\u20131 against them in the first leg.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United 1-2 Swindon: Nathan Byrne's late strike hands Robins advantage|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/sheff-utd-vs-swindon/336760|publisher=Sky Sports|date=8 May 2015|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Despite this, he finished his first season, making 50 appearances (20 league) in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2015\u201316 season, Basham continued to be in the first team regular at the club following the arrival of Manager [[Nigel Adkins]] and then played his first match as captain against [[Doncaster Rovers F.C.|Doncaster Rovers]] on 26 September 2015, scoring his first goal of the season, in a 3\u20131 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United 3 - 1 Doncaster Rovers|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34299158|website=BBC Sport|date=26 September 2015|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Throughout the 2015\u201316 season, Basham went on to captain on five occasions following [[Jay McEveley]]'s absence.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-chris-basham-2722299.aspx|title=Captain Bash|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=2 October 2015|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214194721/http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-chris-basham-2722299.aspx|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Basham's second goal of the season came on 28 November 2015, in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Barnsley 1-1 Sheffield United: Late strike from Tykes blunts Blades|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/barnsley-vs-sheff-utd/340311|website=BBC Sport|date=28 November 2015|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Basham also scored two more goals later in the season against [[Colchester United F.C.|Colchester United]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Colchester United 1-2 Sheffield United|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/35269977|website=BBC Sport|date=16 January 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> and [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United 2-0 Walsall: Blade dent Saddlers' promotion hopes|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/sheff-utd-vs-walsall/340560|publisher=Sky Sports|date=2 April 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Despite missing out two league matches, due to injuries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-nigel-adkins-2924652.aspx|title=Trio expected to return|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=29 January 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214200413/http://www.sufc.co.uk/news/article/sheffield-united-nigel-adkins-2924652.aspx|archivedate=14 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Blades boss reveals his trust in latest starlet Ben Whiteman|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/blades-boss-reveals-his-trust-in-latest-starlet-ben-whiteman-1-7795822|publisher=The Star|date=15 March 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> and Basham made 49 (44 league) appearances and scoring four times in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2016\u201317 season, Basham continued to be in the first team regular at the club following the arrival of Manager [[Chris Wilder]] and played in the midfield position.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: Louis Reed hopes for more of a chance under Blades boss Chris Wilder|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-chris-wilder-on-the-lessons-of-non-league-1-8155595|publisher=The Star|date=11 September 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Basham then scored his first goal of the season, but was later sent-off in the second half, in a 2\u20132 draw against [[Scunthorpe United F.C.|Scunthorpe United]] on 24 September 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Scunthorpe United 2 \u2013 2 Sheffield United|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37392621|website=BBC Sport|date=24 September 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> After serving a three match suspension,<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: Chris Basham will not face internal investigation after being sent-off at Scunthorpe United|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-chris-basham-will-not-face-internal-investigation-after-being-sent-off-at-scunthorpe-1-8147631|publisher=The Star|date=27 September 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Basham returned to the first team, on 18 October 2016, making his first start from suspension, in a 3\u20130 win against [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Billy Sharp doubles-up to tame Shrews - Shrewsbury Town 0 Sheffield United|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/billy-sharp-doubles-up-to-tame-shrews-shrewsbury-town-0-sheffield-united-3-1-8188320|publisher=The Star|date=18 October 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> followed up by scoring in the next game, in a 3\u20133 draw against [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bradford City 3 - 3 Sheffield United|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37663456|website=BBC Sport|date=22 October 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Two weeks later, on 6 November 2016, Basham scored and set up one of the goals, in a 6\u20130 win over [[Leyton Orient F.C.|Leyton Orient]] in the first round of the FA Cup.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United 6 - 0 Leyton Orient|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37813896|website=BBC Sport|date=6 November 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> Due to his impressive performance at the club, Manager Wilder hinted that Basham could be earning a new contract, with a year to his contract left.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: Blades stars are set for new deals|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-blades-stars-are-set-for-new-deals-1-8288244|publisher=The Star|date=14 December 2016|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> As the 2016\u201317 season progressed, Basham began to play in the defense, as a centre-back, partnering with either [[Jack O'Connell (footballer)|Jack O'Connell]], [[Ethan Ebanks-Landell]] and [[Jake Wright]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: Leon Clarke out for a month with ankle injury|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-leon-clarke-out-for-a-month-with-ankle-injury-1-8145720|publisher=The Star|date=25 November 2016|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: Former Bolton star Chris Basham wants to prove nice guys can finish first|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-former-bolton-star-chris-basham-wants-to-prove-nice-guys-can-finish-first-1-8406140|publisher=The Star|date=24 February 2017|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref> Around the same time, Basham played in the midfield position, with [[Paul Coutts]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: John Fleck set to receive the go-ahead|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-john-fleck-set-to-receive-the-go-ahead-1-8185903|publisher=The Star|date=18 October 2016|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref> Then, in a 3\u20130 win over [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] on 14 April 2017, Basham produced an impressive display when he set up two goals.<ref>{{cite news|title=Match Report: Port Vale 0, Sheffield United 3|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/match-report-port-vale-0-sheffield-united-3-1-8494299|publisher=The Star|date=14 April 2017|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref> At the end of the 2016\u201317 season, which saw Sheffield United promoted to [[EFL Championship|Championship]] after six seasons in League One, Basham went on to make 48 appearances and scoring two times in all competitions.\n\nIn July 2017, Basham penned a new two-year contract with the Blades having played a key role in United's title winning promotion from League One.<ref>{{cite news|title=New Contracts|url=https://www.sufc.co.uk/news/2017/july/new-contracts/|publisher=Sheffield United FC|date=18 July 2017|accessdate=18 July 2017}}</ref> On 28 April 2019, Basham saw his second promotion in three seasons with United as the Blades were promoted to the [[Premier League]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48026965|title=Sheffield United promoted to Premier League after Leeds draw|website=BBC Sport|date=2019-04-28|access-date=2019-04-30}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBorn in [[Hebburn]],<ref name=Hugman/> Basham studied at [[Gateshead College]] and trained with their [[Gateshead International Stadium|Academy for Sport]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Basham loving life in the first team|url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/4039542.Basham_loving_life_in_the_first_team/|publisher=The Bolton News|date=12 January 2009|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> He grew up supporting [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]].<ref name=\"sunderland support\">{{cite web|url=http://www.blackpoolgazette.co.uk/sport/blackpool-fc/sunderland-fan-can-t-wait-for-crack-at-newcastle-1-5896590|title=Sunderland fan can't wait for crack at Newcastle|publisher=Blackpool Gazette|date=28 July 2013|accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> Basham considers [[Alan Cork]] as a great influence and is indebted to Cork for guiding him throughout his professional football career.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United: Why Chris Basham owes a debt of gratitude to Alan Cork|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-why-chris-basham-owes-a-debt-of-gratitude-to-alan-cork-1-8269531|publisher=The Star|date=2 December 2016|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nHaving two years away from football, after leaving Newcastle United at sixteen, Basham worked at [[McDonald's]].<ref name=\"Basham2\">{{cite news|title=Basham goes from Big Mac to big break|url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/3850102.Basham_goes_from_Big_Mac_to_big_break/|publisher=The Bolton News|date=15 November 2008|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> In late 2014, Basham became a father.<ref name=\"BashamSUFC\"/>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|06 May 2019}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n! colspan=\"3\" |League\n! colspan=\"2\" |FA Cup\n! colspan=\"2\" |League Cup\n! colspan=\"2\" |Other\n! colspan=\"2\" |Total\n|-\n!Division||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals\n|-\n|[[Stafford Rangers F.C.|Stafford Rangers]] (loan)\n|[[2006\u201307 Football Conference|2006\u201307]]<ref name=\"0607stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2006|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|[[Conference National]]\n|3||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||4||0\n|-\n|[[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]] (loan)\n|[[2007\u201308 Rochdale A.F.C. season|2007\u201308]]<ref name=\"0708stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2007|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|[[Football League Two|League Two]]\n|13||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||13||0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]]\n|[[2008\u201309 Bolton Wanderers F.C. season|2008\u201309]]<ref name=\"0809stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2008|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Premier League]]\n|11||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||11||1\n|-\n|[[2009\u201310 Bolton Wanderers F.C. season|2009\u201310]]<ref name=\"0910stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2009|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|8||0||1||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||10||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!19||1||1||0||1||0|| colspan=\"2\" |'''\u2014'''||21||1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]]\n|[[2010\u201311 Blackpool F.C. season|2010\u201311]]<ref name=\"1011stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2010|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|2||0||0||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||3||0\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Blackpool F.C. season|2011\u201312]]<ref name=\"1112stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2011|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Football League Championship|Championship]]\n|17||2||3||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||21||2\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Blackpool F.C. season|2012\u201313]]<ref name=\"1213stats\">{{Soccerbase season|45672|2012|name=Chris Basham|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n|26||1||2||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u