02090222/http://bestapples.com/varieties-information/varieties/ |archivedate=2 July 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Further reading==\n'''Books'''\n* {{cite book |last=Browning |first=F. |year=1999 |title=Apples: The Story of the Fruit of Temptation |url= |location= |publisher=North Point Press |page= |isbn=978-0-86547-579-3}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Mabberley |first1=D.J |last2=Juniper |first2=B.E |year=2009 |title=The Story of the Apple |url= |location= |publisher=Timber Press |isbn=978-1-60469-172-6}}\n* {{cite news\n| date         = 2 November 1933\n| title        = Humor and Philosophy Relating to Apples\n| url          = https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1955&dat=19331102&id=KmYhAAAAIBAJ&sjid=vYcFAAAAIBAJ&pg=2364,365296\n| work         = [[Reading Eagle]]\n| location     = Reading, PA\n| access-date  = 24 May 2019\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Apples}}\n* {{Britannica|30599|Apple (fruit and tree)}}\n* [http://www.catalogueoflife.org/col/details/species/id/52b2255cff5bc2b40778e3e4a2c7be71 ''Malus pumila'' Mill. (accepted name)]\n{{Apples}}\n{{Crabapple}}\n{{taxonbar|from=Q158657|from2=Q18674606}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Apples|*]]\n[[Category:Malus|*]]\n[[Category:Fruits originating in Asia]]\n[[Category:Plants described in 1768]]\n", "name_user": "Lotje", "label": "safe", "comment": "(GR)File renamed:File:Aroma.jpg\u2192File:Aroma (apple).jpg#2", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apple"}
{"title_page": "Marlene Kahler", "text_new": "{{short description|Austrian swimmer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox swimmer\n| name           = Marlene Kahler\n| image          = 2018-10-10 Swimming Girls' 200m Freestyle Final at 2018 Summer Youth Olympics by Sandro Halank\u2013034.jpg\n| caption        = Marlene Kahler, 2018\n| fullname       = \n| nationality    = Austrian\n| strokes        = \n| club           = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|2001|5|15|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = \n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| show-medals    = \n| medaltemplates = \n}}\n'''Marlene Kahler''' (born 15 May 2001) is an Austrian [[Swimming (sport)|swimmer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.noen.at/sport/bruck/im-interview-marlene-kahler-stimmung-war-top-die-mahlzeit-ein-flop-marlene-kahler-schwimmen-noen-interview-122099463 |title=Marlene Kahler: Stimmung war top, die Mahlzeit ein Flop |work=noen.at |accessdate=30 July 2019}}</ref> She competed in the [[Swimming at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships \u2013 Women's 200 metre freestyle|women's 200 metre freestyle]] at the [[2019 World Aquatics Championships]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://omegatiming.com/File/00011301070201EE01FFFFFFFFFFFF00.pdf |title=18th FINA World Championships 2019: Women's 200m Freestyle start list |work=FINA |accessdate=30 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721095419/http://omegatiming.com/File/00011301070201EE01FFFFFFFFFFFF00.pdf |archive-date=21 July 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kahler, Marlene}}\n[[Category:2001 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Austrian female swimmers]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Swimmers at the 2018 Summer Youth Olympics]]\n{{Austria-swimming-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Austrian swimmer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox swimmer\n| name           = Marlene Kahler\n| image          = 2018-10-10 Swimming Girls' 200m Freestyle Final at 2018 Summer Youth Olympics by Sandro Halank\u2013034.jpg\n| caption        = Marlene Kahler, 2018\n| fullname       = \n| nationality    = Austrian\n| strokes        = \n| club           = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|2001|5|15|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = \n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| show-medals    = \n| medaltemplates = \n}}\n'''Marlene Kahler''' (born 15 May 2001) is an Austrian [[Swimming (sport)|swimmer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.noen.at/sport/bruck/im-interview-marlene-kahler-stimmung-war-top-die-mahlzeit-ein-flop-marlene-kahler-schwimmen-noen-interview-122099463 |title=Marlene Kahler: Stimmung war top, die Mahlzeit ein Flop |work=noen.at |accessdate=30 July 2019}}</ref> She competed in the [[Swimming at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships \u2013 Women's 200 metre freestyle|women's 200 metre freestyle]] at the [[2019 World Aquatics Championships]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://omegatiming.com/File/00011301070201EE01FFFFFFFFFFFF00.pdf |title=18th FINA World Championships 2019: Women's 200m Freestyle start list |work=FINA |accessdate=30 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721095419/http://omegatiming.com/File/00011301070201EE01FFFFFFFFFFFF00.pdf |archive-date=21 July 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kahler, Marlene}}\n[[Category:2001 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Austrian female swimmers]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Swimmers at the 2018 Summer Youth Olympics]]\n{{Austria-swimming-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marlene_Kahler"}
{"title_page": "Indian locomotive class WAP-7", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox locomotive\n| name             = WAP-7\n| image            = File:WAP-7-LOCO.jpg\n| caption          =  A newly bulit WAP-7 at [[Chittaranjan Locomotive Works|CLW]]\n| powertype        = [[Electric locomotive|Electric]]\n| builder          = [[Chittaranjan Locomotive Works]],<br />[[Diesel Locomotive Works]],<ref name=\"prod_dlw\" /><br />[[Diesel-Loco Modernisation Works]]\n| builddate        = 10 May 2000 - present\n| totalproduction  = 1047 as of April 2020\n| gauge            = {{Track gauge|5ft6in|lk=on}}\n| bogies           = [[Co-Co locomotives|Co-Co]], Fabricated [[Flexicoil]] Mark IV [[bogie]]s; bogie wheelbase {{convert|1850|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}} + {{convert|1850|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n| wheeldiameter    = {{convert|1092|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}} new, {{convert|1016|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}} worn\n| wheelbase        = {{convert|15700|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n| length           = \n|  over couplers   = \n|  over bufferbeams= {{convert|20562|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|  body            = \n| width            = {{convert|3152|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n| height           = \n|  pantodown       = {{convert|4255|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|  bodyonly        = <!-- electrics -->\n| axleload         = '''WAP 7'''<br>\n{{convert|20.5|t|abbr=on}}\n\n'''WAP 7HS'''\n{{convert|18.08|t|abbr=on}}\n| locoweight       = {{convert|123|t|abbr=on}}\n| powersupply      = 3-phase 2180 V 50 Hz\n| electricsystem   = [[25 kV 50 Hz|25 kV 50 Hz AC]] [[Overhead line|Overhead]]\n| collectionmethod = [[pantograph (rail)|Pantograph]] \n| tractionmotors   = 6FRA 6068 3-phase squirrel-cage induction motors<br />{{convert|850|kW|abbr=on}}, 2180 V, 1283/2484 rpm, 270/310A;<br />Weight-{{convert|2100|kg|abbr=on}}, forced-air ventilation, axle-hung, nose-suspended;<br />Torque {{convert|6330|-|7140|Nm|abbr=on}}<br />~88% efficiency.<!-- Efficiency is P.in/P.out - Six traction motors rated at 850kW each (5100kW input) give 4474kw output - 87.72% efficiency -->\n| transmission     = Electric\n| gear ratio       = '''WAP 7''' <br>72:20 <br> '''WAP 7HS''' <br>70:22\n| locobrakes       = [[railway air brake|Air]] and [[regenerative brake|regenerative]]\n| trainbrakes      = [[Railway air brake|Air]]\n| maxspeed         = {{convert|140|km/h|mph|abbr=on}} \n| poweroutput      = Continuous : {{convert|6122|HP|kW|abbr=on}}\n| tractiveeffort   = Starting : {{convert|322.4|kN|lbf|abbr=on}}\n<br />Continuous : {{convert|228|kN|lbf|abbr=on}} at 71 km/h\n| operator         = [[Indian Railways]]\n| fleetnumbers     = '''30201+''' [[Chittaranjan Locomotive Works|CLW]]\n'''37001+''' [[Diesel Locomotive Works|DLW]]\n'''39000+''' [[Diesel-Loco Modernisation Works|DLMW]]\n| firstrundate     = 19 May 2000<ref>{{cite web|title=Indian Railways Locomotive: 30201|url=http://www.irfca.org/apps/locos/show/9389?authenticity_token=G98a69ZQavZkM4OaLo1EvHeYRnbG%2FkPl8kbtDXFLXJY%3D&loco_class_id=43&page=1|publisher=IRFCA|accessdate=30 December 2017}}</ref>\n| nicknames        = \n| locale           = [[India]]\n}}\n\nThe '''WAP 7''' ([[5 ft 6 in gauge railway|Wide/broad Gauge]] ''A''[[25 kV AC railway electrification|C Electric]] ''P''assenger, Class ''7'') is a [[three-phase]] AC electric passenger [[locomotive]] developed by the [[Chittaranjan Locomotive Works]]. It is the most powerful passenger locomotive in the Indian Railways' fleet. It is a passenger variant of the [[Indian locomotive class WAG-9|WAG 9]] freight locomotive with a modified [[gear ratio]] to pull lighter loads at higher speeds. It is capable of hauling 24 coach trains at speeds ranging {{convert|110|-|140|km/h|abbr=on}}, depending on the MPS (Maximum Permissible Speed) of the sector, and is now largely used by [[Northern Railway (India)|Northern Railways]] (NR), [[South Central Railway zone|South Central Railway]] (SCR), [[Central Railways]] (CR), [[South East Central Railway Zone]] (SECR), [[South Eastern Railway (India)|South Eastern Railways]] (SER), [[West Central Railway zone|West Central Railways]] (WCR), [[Eastern Railway zone|Eastern Railways]] (ER), [[Western Railway zone]] (WR), [[North Central Railway zone]] (NCR), [[South Western Railway zone|South Western Railway]] (SWR) etc among other zones. As of April 2020, there are 1046 locomotives in service, all of which are fitted with [[tightlock coupler]]s (for [[Buffers and chain coupler#Center-buffer-and-chain(s)|central buffer coupling]]) and chain link couplers. In February 2017, [[Diesel Locomotive Works]] built their first WAP 7 class locomotive.<ref name=\"prod_dlw\">{{cite web|title=Brief History of DLW|url=http://www.dlw.indianrailways.gov.in/view_section.jsp?lang=0&id=0,294,702|publisher=Ministry of Railways, Government of India|accessdate=30 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Performance==\nWith a maximum speed rating of {{convert|140|km/h|abbr=on}} the WAP-7 has the highest acceleration figures while hauling mail/express trains. The WAP-7 can also haul loads of 24-26 passenger coaches ({{convert|1430|\u2013|1550|t|abbr=on|disp=or}} at {{convert|130|km/h|abbr=on|disp=or}}). It is the most successful passenger locomotive on the Indian Railways roster after the [[Indian locomotive class WAP-4|WAP 4]]. It was initially used to haul premium train services like the [[Rajdhani Express]], [[Shatabdi Express]] and the [[Duronto Express]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2012-02-09/news/31041825_1_nagpur-division-high-speed-passenger |title=New energy-efficient loco introduced for high speed train |newspaper=[[The Economic Times|Economic Times]] |date=9 Feb 2012|accessdate=25 Aug 2012}}</ref> As more locomotives were rolled out, the WAP 7 became the official link of several ''state trains'' like the [[Telangana Express]], [[Kerala Express]], [[Paschim Express]], [[Purushottam Express|Purushottam express]], [[Vikramshila Express|Vikramshila express]], [[Poorva Express|Poorva express]],[[Karnataka Express|Karnataka express]] and among others. The locomotives have been used as a regular link for many of the [[Garib Rath Express|Garib Rath express]] and many [[Humsafar Express|Humsafar express]]<nowiki/>services and eventually extended to a significant number of [[AC Express (Indian Railways)|AC Express]] and [[Superfast/Mail Trains in India|Mail/Superfast Express]] services like [[Jaipur Superfast Express]], [[Thiruvananthapuram Mail]], [[Mangalore Mail]], [[Bangalore Mail]], [[Sewagram Express|Sewagram]] express and so on. It is soon to be the most commonly used passenger locomotive. Upgrades are underway to increase power output and maximum speed. The First High Speed version WAP-7 HS loco ( loco no 30750) was launched on 28 February 2019 capable of attaining 160 km/h with overall reduction in weight by 14 tons.\n\n[[File:WAP730333.jpg|thumb|30333 WAP-7 locomotive of RPM ([[Royapuram Railway Station|Royapuram]]) shed at [[Mysore|Mysuru]], [[Karnataka]].]]\nThe WAP-7 locomotive can deliver {{convert|6125|hp|kW|abbr=on|lk=on}} continuously, with [[Regenerative brake|regenerative braking]] being one of its salient features. Regenerative braking is deployed on down gradients conserving energy to the tune of 30-35 percent. It has an inbuilt microprocessor based fault diagnostic system to make troubleshooting easier.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/states/tamil-nadu/southern-railway-inducts-fast-locomotive/article4006756.ece |title=Southern Railway inducts fast locomotive |newspaper=The Hindu |date=18 Oct 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Head-on Generation (HOG)==\nA main feature of some locomotives of this class is that they eliminate the need to have separate End on Generation (EOG) sets or DG (Diesel Generator) sets for supplying power to the train resulting in significant savings on maintenance and running costs. This technology, called HOG or \"Head On Generation\", transfers electric power from the loco's [[Pantograph (transport)|pantograph]] to the coaches instead of EOG where a power car equipped with diesel generator capable of generating adequate power of 3-phase 50&nbsp;Hz 415 V / 750 V AC (called '[[head-end power]]') is provided at either end of the train rake to supply power.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/train-had-wap7-engine-black-box-may-reveal-cause/816265/0 |title=Train had WAP-7 engine, \u2018black box\u2019 may reveal cause|publisher=[[Zee News]]|date=9 Aug 2010|accessdate=25 Aug 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clw.indianrailways.gov.in/view_section.jsp?lang=0&id=0,296,306,470|title=Recent Developments |publisher=[[Chittaranjan Loco works]] |accessdate=25 Aug 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"rdso\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rdso.indianrailways.gov.in/works/uploads/File/Electrical(1).pdf |title=Development of Electric locomotive with Head On Generation (HOG) facility |publisher=Indian Railways}}</ref>\n\n==Technical Specifications==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Technical Specifications<ref name=\"irfca\">{{cite web |url=http://www.irfca.org/faq/faq-loco2e.html#loco |title=Recent Developments |publisher=IRFCA}}</ref>\n|Manufacturers || Chittaranjan Locomotive Works (CLW)<br />Diesel Locomotive Works (DLW)<br />Diesel Locomotive Modernisation Works\n|-\n|Traction Motors || 6FRA 6068 3-phase squirrel-cage induction motors<br />{{convert|850|kW|abbr=on}}, 2180 V, 1283/2484 rpm, 270/310A;<br />Weight-{{convert|2100|kg|abbr=on}}, forced-air ventilation, axle-hung, nose-suspended;<br />Torque {{convert|6330|-|7140|Nm|abbr=on}}<br />~88% efficiency.<!-- Efficiency is P.in/P.out - Six traction motors rated at 850kW each (5100kW input) give 4474kw output - 87.72% efficiency -->\n|-\n|[[Gear Ratio]] || 72:20    , 70:22( for HS Version)\n|-\n|[[Axle load]] || {{convert|20.5|t|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|Wheel diameter || {{convert|1092|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}} new, {{convert|1016|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}} worn\n|-\n|[[Wheelbase]] || {{convert|15700|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|-\n|[[Bogie]]s || [[Co-Co locomotives|Co-Co]], Fabricated [[Flexicoil]] Mark IV [[bogie]]s; bogie wheelbase {{convert|1850|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}} + {{convert|1850|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|-\n|Unsprung mass per axle || {{convert|3.984|t|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|Length over [[Buffer (rail transport)|buffers]] || {{convert|20562|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|-\n|Length over [[Headstock (rolling stock)|headstocks]] || {{convert|19280|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}} \n|-\n|Body width || {{convert|3152|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|-\n|loco weight || {{convert|123|t|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|Cab length || {{convert|2434|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|-\n|Pantograph locked down height || {{convert|4255|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|}\n\n==Locomotive Sheds==\n[[File:Yesvantpur bound Express from Tatanagar enters Pithapuram with a WAP7 Locomotive.jpg|alt=|thumb|Lallaguda WAP7]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Zone !! Shed Code !! Name \n!Quantity!! Introduction !! Out of Service !! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |CR || AJNI ||[[Ajni railway station|Ajni]]\n|63|| 27 December 2010 || 1 (WAP-7 #30270 is out of service due to accident damage) || First loco transferred from GZB.Locomotive WAP-7 30543 of this shed named \"OJAS\"\n|-\n|KYN\n|[[Loco Shed, Kalyan|Kalyan]]\n|25\n|21 June 2019\n|\n|First loco transferred from AJNI.used for PushPull Technology.\n|-\n|ER || HWH ||[[Howrah railway station|Howrah]]\n|76|| 20 February 2012 ||  || First loco transferred from GMO; holds the 150th electric locomotive WAP7 37025 of this shed, named \"ASWAMEDH\"\n|-\n| ER || BGA || [[Beliaghata Road railway station]] ||10|| ||  || ||  ||\n|-\n|ECR\n|GMO\n|[[Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose Gomoh railway station|Gomoh]]\n|46\n|15 November 2018\n|\n|Recently started Holding WAP7 locos,  serve all routes across [[West Central Railway zone|East Central Railway zone]]. First WAP 7 shed for ECR\n|-\n|NR || GZB ||[[Ghaziabad railway station|Ghaziabad]]\n|152|| 19 May 2000 ||  || First WAP-7 was operated by NR and Indian Railways\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |WCR || TKD ||[[Tughlakabad railway station|Tughlakabad]]\n|87|| 25 January 2013 ||  || First loco transferred from GZB\n\n|-\n| ET ||[[Itarsi Junction railway station|Itarsi]]\n|25|| 1 December 2018 ||  ||Holds 100th DLW WAP7 37073, nicknamed\"SHATAK\".\n|-\n|NCR\n|CNB\n|[[Kanpur Central railway station|Kanpur]]\n|40\n|31 March 2019\n|\n|First loco shed in [[North Central Railway zone]] to hold WAP7 locos\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |SR || RPM ||[[Royapuram railway station|Royapuram]]\n|102|| 21 January 2011 ||  ||First WAP7 locomotive shed of Southern Railway.Holds WAP7 30479, nicknamed\"THANGAM\".\n|-\n| ED ||[[ Electric Loco Shed, Erode|Erode]]\n|37|| 19 October 2017 ||  || First loco transferred from RPM.Holds the WAP7 30573, nicknamed\"CAUVERY\".\n|-\n| SCR || LGD || [[Lallaguda railway station|Lallaguda]] \n|112|| 26 December 2008 ||  ||First WAP7 loco shed for [[South India]] next to [[Ghaziabad, Uttar Pradesh|Ghaziabad.]] 100th WAP-7 Nicknamed \"SHATASHV\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |SER\n|SRC\n|[[Santragachi Junction railway station|Santragachi]]\n|39\n|9 November 2017\n|\n|First loco transferred from GMO\nSER\n|-\n| TATA ||[[Tatanagar Junction railway station|Tatanagar]]\n|38|| 18 April 2017 ||  ||First WAP7 locomotive shed for [[South Eastern Railway zone]].(Located in extreme South eastern of [[Jharkhand]] state).\n|-\n|BNDM\n|[[Bondamunda railway station|Bondamunda]]\n|15\n|31 August 2019\n|\n|First locomotive transferred from [[Tatanagar Junction railway station|Tatanagar]] shed. third WAP-7 shed of [[South Eastern Railway zone]]\n|-\n| SECR || BIA ||[[Bhilai]]\n|54|| 6 September 2012 ||  || First loco transferred from GMO\n|-\n| SWR || KJM ||[[Krishnarajapuram railway station|Krishnarajapuram]]\n|5|| 29 July 2019 ||  ||First WAP7 locomotive shed of South Western Railways.1st WAP7 30576 transfer from Royapuram Shed, nicknamed\"CHAMUNDI\".\n|-\n| WR || BRC ||[[Vadodara Junction railway station|Vadodara]]\n|87|| 23 April 2016 ||  ||First WAP7 locomotive shed for Western Railway zone. Shed consists more HOG locos then Non-HOG.\n|-\n| ECoR/SCoR || VSKP ||[[Visakhapatnam railway station|Visakhapatnam]]\n|33|| 22 November 2016 ||  ||First WAP7 locomotive shed for ECoR/SCoR zone.\n|-\n| Total Locomotives Active as of 01-04-2020  ||\n|| ||1046||  ||\n|}('''Note-'''Before updating the information here anybody should check out the railways current official data first in the  '''Source''' link then change the data.)\n'''Source:'''http://elocos.railnet.gov.in/Loco_bank/shedwise.aspx\n\n==Named Locos==\n[[File:A Ghaziabad based Head On Generation (HOG) WAP-7 hauling Bhubaneswar Rajdhani Express.jpg|thumb|A Ghaziabad-based Head On Generation (HOG) WAP-7 hauling Bhubaneswar Rajdhani Express at Balasore, Odisha]]\n* WAP-7 30201 Navkiran (GZB)\n* WAP-7 30202 Navbharti (BIA)\n* WAP-7 30209 Navchetak (GZB)\n* WAP-7 30215 Navgati (GZB)\n* WAP-7 30227 Champalal (GZB)\n* WAP-7 30295 Navjyoti (HWH)\n* WAP-7 30479 Thangam (RPM)\n* WAP-7 30509 Varun (GZB)\n* WAP-7 30521 Varun (GZB)\n* WAP-7 30543 Ojas (AJNI)\n* WAP-7 30573 Cauvery (ED)\n* WAP-7 30576 Chamundi (KJM)\n* WAP-7 30622 Sharavathi (KJM)\n* WAP-7 30630 Kabini (KJM)\n* WAP-7 30631 Hemavathi (KJM)\n* WAP-7 37015 Tunga (KJM)\n* WAP-7 37025 Ashwamedh (HWH)\n* WAP-7 37073 Shatak (ET)\n* WAP-7 37085 Shatashv (LGD)\n* WAP-7 37215 Platinum (HWH)\n* WAP-7 37222 Bhavani (ED)\n\n==Liveries==\n\n* This locomotive's common livery is white, black & single red band.\n\n* '''Royapuram''' Electric Loco Shed has '''Sharon Plywood''' advertisement on loco's body side.\n\n* '''Tatanagar''' Electric Loco Shed has '''TATA Steel''' advertisement on loco's body side.\n\n* '''Ajni''' Electric Loco Shed has '''Haldiram's Sweets & Namkeens''' advertisement on loco's body side.\n\n* '''Bhilai''' Electric Loco Shed has '''Goel TMT''' advertisement on loco's body side.\n\n*'''Erode''' Electric Loco Shed has '''Porna Chicken''' advertisement on loco's body side.\n\n==Accidents==\nOn 10 July 2011, [[Kalka Mail]] derailed on the Kanpur-Fatehpur line near the [[Fatehpur railway station]], more than 72 persons died and 200 were injured, some critically. The train was hauled by a Ghaziabad-based WAP 7 30221. Malfunction of the undergear of the locomotive may have been a reason. The driver of the Kalka Mail said he saw the engine shaking.<ref name=\"IBN Live\">{{cite news |title=Engine failure behind Kalka Mail tragedy |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/engine-failure-behind-kalka-mail-tragedy/167288-3.html |accessdate=14 July 2011 |publisher=IBN Live |date=13 July 2011}}</ref> A post-accident diagnostic revealed that the first axle (leading) of the locomotive registered a jerk and the fourth axle (trailing bogie) showed loss of contact of the wheel with the track.<ref>{{cite web|title=Death by Design|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/faulty-rail-engines-lead-to-accidents/1/145012.html|publisher=Living Media India Limited.|accessdate=31 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 December 2014, the [[Howrah]] - [[New Delhi]] [[Poorva Express]] derailed shortly after leaving [[Howrah]], Kolkata. 11 sleeper coaches and a pantry car (A/C hot buffer car) of the rake jumped the rails in the incident. Due to the derailment occurring when the train was just skipping [[Liluah]], and the usage of [[LHB coaches]], the accident was contained and no casualties were reported. Like the 2011 Kalka Mail derailment, this accident also involved a Howrah-based WAP 7 locomotive.<ref>{{cite web|title=12 coaches of Poorva Express derail, no casualty|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/cities/kolkata/12-coaches-of-poorva-express-derail-no-casualty/|publisher=The Indian Express [P] Ltd.|accessdate=31 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Indian Railways]]\n*[[History of rail transport in India]]\n*[[Locomotives of India]]\n*[[Rail transport in India]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Indian locomotive class WAP7}}\n*[http://www.irfca.org IRFCA-Indian Railways Fan Club]\n*[http://www.clwindia.com CLW Railways India]\n*[http://www.irfca.org/faq/faq-loco2e.html Notes on electric locos from IRFCA-Indian Railways Fan Club]\n*[http://trainspo.com/class/510/ IR WAP-7 @ Trainspo]\n\n{{Broad gauge locomotives of India}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Indian Locomotive Class Wap-7}}\n[[Category:5 ft 6 in gauge locomotives]]\n[[Category:25 kV AC locomotives]]\n[[Category:Co-Co locomotives]]\n[[Category:Electric locomotives of India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox locomotive\n| name             = WAP-7\n| image            = File:WAP-7-LOCO.jpg\n| caption          =  A newly bulit WAP-7 at [[Chittaranjan Locomotive Works|CLW]]\n| powertype        = [[Electric locomotive|Electric]]\n| builder          = [[Chittaranjan Locomotive Works]],<br />[[Diesel Locomotive Works]],<ref name=\"prod_dlw\" /><br />[[Diesel-Loco Modernisation Works]]\n| builddate        = 10 May 2000 - present\n| totalproduction  = 1047 as of April 2020\n| gauge            = {{Track gauge|5ft6in|lk=on}}\n| bogies           = [[Co-Co locomotives|Co-Co]], Fabricated [[Flexicoil]] Mark IV [[bogie]]s; bogie wheelbase {{convert|1850|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}} + {{convert|1850|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n| wheeldiameter    = {{convert|1092|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}} new, {{convert|1016|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}} worn\n| wheelbase        = {{convert|15700|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n| length           = \n|  over couplers   = \n|  over bufferbeams= {{convert|20562|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|  body            = \n| width            = {{convert|3152|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n| height           = \n|  pantodown       = {{convert|4255|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|  bodyonly        = <!-- electrics -->\n| axleload         = '''WAP 7'''<br>\n{{convert|20.5|t|abbr=on}}\n\n'''WAP 7HS'''\n{{convert|18.08|t|abbr=on}}\n| locoweight       = {{convert|123|t|abbr=on}}\n| powersupply      = 3-phase 2180 V 50 Hz\n| electricsystem   = [[25 kV 50 Hz|25 kV 50 Hz AC]] [[Overhead line|Overhead]]\n| collectionmethod = [[pantograph (rail)|Pantograph]] \n| tractionmotors   = 6FRA 6068 3-phase squirrel-cage induction motors<br />{{convert|850|kW|abbr=on}}, 2180 V, 1283/2484 rpm, 270/310A;<br />Weight-{{convert|2100|kg|abbr=on}}, forced-air ventilation, axle-hung, nose-suspended;<br />Torque {{convert|6330|-|7140|Nm|abbr=on}}<br />~88% efficiency.<!-- Efficiency is P.in/P.out - Six traction motors rated at 850kW each (5100kW input) give 4474kw output - 87.72% efficiency -->\n| transmission     = Electric\n| gear ratio       = '''WAP 7''' <br>72:20 <br> '''WAP 7HS''' <br>70:22\n| locobrakes       = [[railway air brake|Air]] and [[regenerative brake|regenerative]]\n| trainbrakes      = [[Railway air brake|Air]]\n| maxspeed         = {{convert|140|km/h|mph|abbr=on}} \n| poweroutput      = Continuous : {{convert|6122|HP|kW|abbr=on}}\n| tractiveeffort   = Starting : {{convert|322.4|kN|lbf|abbr=on}}\n<br />Continuous : {{convert|228|kN|lbf|abbr=on}} at 71 km/h\n| operator         = [[Indian Railways]]\n| fleetnumbers     = '''30201+''' [[Chittaranjan Locomotive Works|CLW]]\n'''37001+''' [[Diesel Locomotive Works|DLW]]\n'''39000+''' [[Diesel-Loco Modernisation Works|DLMW]]\n| firstrundate     = 19 May 2000<ref>{{cite web|title=Indian Railways Locomotive: 30201|url=http://www.irfca.org/apps/locos/show/9389?authenticity_token=G98a69ZQavZkM4OaLo1EvHeYRnbG%2FkPl8kbtDXFLXJY%3D&loco_class_id=43&page=1|publisher=IRFCA|accessdate=30 December 2017}}</ref>\n| nicknames        = \n| locale           = [[India]]\n}}\n\nThe '''WAP 7''' ([[5 ft 6 in gauge railway|Wide/broad Gauge]] ''A''[[25 kV AC railway electrification|C Electric]] ''P''assenger, Class ''7'') is a [[three-phase]] AC electric passenger [[locomotive]] developed by the [[Chittaranjan Locomotive Works]]. It is the most powerful passenger locomotive in the Indian Railways' fleet. It is a passenger variant of the [[Indian locomotive class WAG-9|WAG 9]] freight locomotive with a modified [[gear ratio]] to pull lighter loads at higher speeds. It is capable of hauling 24 coach trains at speeds ranging {{convert|110|-|140|km/h|abbr=on}}, depending on the MPS (Maximum Permissible Speed) of the sector, and is now largely used by [[Northern Railway (India)|Northern Railways]] (NR), [[South Central Railway zone|South Central Railway]] (SCR), [[Central Railways]] (CR), [[South East Central Railway Zone]] (SECR), [[South Eastern Railway (India)|South Eastern Railways]] (SER), [[West Central Railway zone|West Central Railways]] (WCR), [[Eastern Railway zone|Eastern Railways]] (ER), [[Western Railway zone]] (WR), [[North Central Railway zone]] (NCR), [[South Western Railway zone|South Western Railway]] (SWR) etc among other zones. As of April 2020, there are 1046 locomotives in service, all of which are fitted with [[tightlock coupler]]s (for [[Buffers and chain coupler#Center-buffer-and-chain(s)|central buffer coupling]]) and chain link couplers. In February 2017, [[Diesel Locomotive Works]] built their first WAP 7 class locomotive.<ref name=\"prod_dlw\">{{cite web|title=Brief History of DLW|url=http://www.dlw.indianrailways.gov.in/view_section.jsp?lang=0&id=0,294,702|publisher=Ministry of Railways, Government of India|accessdate=30 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Performance==\nWith a maximum speed rating of {{convert|140|km/h|abbr=on}} the WAP-7 has the highest acceleration figures while hauling mail/express trains. The WAP-7 can also haul loads of 24-26 passenger coaches ({{convert|1430|\u2013|1550|t|abbr=on|disp=or}} at {{convert|130|km/h|abbr=on|disp=or}}). It is the most successful passenger locomotive on the Indian Railways roster after the [[Indian locomotive class WAP-4|WAP 4]]. It was initially used to haul premium train services like the [[Rajdhani Express]], [[Shatabdi Express]] and the [[Duronto Express]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2012-02-09/news/31041825_1_nagpur-division-high-speed-passenger |title=New energy-efficient loco introduced for high speed train |newspaper=[[The Economic Times|Economic Times]] |date=9 Feb 2012|accessdate=25 Aug 2012}}</ref> As more locomotives were rolled out, the WAP 7 became the official link of several ''state trains'' like the [[Telangana Express]], [[Kerala Express]], [[Paschim Express]], [[Purushottam Express|Purushottam express]], [[Vikramshila Express|Vikramshila express]], [[Poorva Express|Poorva express]],[[Karnataka Express|Karnataka express]] and among others. The locomotives have been used as a regular link for many of the [[Garib Rath Express|Garib Rath express]] and many [[Humsafar Express|Humsafar express]]<nowiki/>services and eventually extended to a significant number of [[AC Express (Indian Railways)|AC Express]] and [[Superfast/Mail Trains in India|Mail/Superfast Express]] services like [[Jaipur Superfast Express]], [[Thiruvananthapuram Mail]], [[Mangalore Mail]], [[Bangalore Mail]], [[Sewagram Express|Sewagram]] express and so on. It is soon to be the most commonly used passenger locomotive. Upgrades are underway to increase power output and maximum speed. The First High Speed version WAP-7 HS loco ( loco no 30750) was launched on 28 February 2019 capable of attaining 160 km/h with overall reduction in weight by 14 tons.\n\n[[File:WAP730333.jpg|thumb|30333 WAP-7 locomotive of RPM ([[Royapuram Railway Station|Royapuram]]) shed at [[Mysore|Mysuru]], [[Karnataka]].]]\nThe WAP-7 locomotive can deliver {{convert|6125|hp|kW|abbr=on|lk=on}} continuously, with [[Regenerative brake|regenerative braking]] being one of its salient features. Regenerative braking is deployed on down gradients conserving energy to the tune of 30-35 percent. It has an inbuilt microprocessor based fault diagnostic system to make troubleshooting easier.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/states/tamil-nadu/southern-railway-inducts-fast-locomotive/article4006756.ece |title=Southern Railway inducts fast locomotive |newspaper=The Hindu |date=18 Oct 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Head-on Generation (HOG)==\nA main feature of some locomotives of this class is that they eliminate the need to have separate End on Generation (EOG) sets or DG (Diesel Generator) sets for supplying power to the train resulting in significant savings on maintenance and running costs. This technology, called HOG or \"Head On Generation\", transfers electric power from the loco's [[Pantograph (transport)|pantograph]] to the coaches instead of EOG where a power car equipped with diesel generator capable of generating adequate power of 3-phase 50&nbsp;Hz 415 V / 750 V AC (called '[[head-end power]]') is provided at either end of the train rake to supply power.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/train-had-wap7-engine-black-box-may-reveal-cause/816265/0 |title=Train had WAP-7 engine, \u2018black box\u2019 may reveal cause|publisher=[[Zee News]]|date=9 Aug 2010|accessdate=25 Aug 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clw.indianrailways.gov.in/view_section.jsp?lang=0&id=0,296,306,470|title=Recent Developments |publisher=[[Chittaranjan Loco works]] |accessdate=25 Aug 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"rdso\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rdso.indianrailways.gov.in/works/uploads/File/Electrical(1).pdf |title=Development of Electric locomotive with Head On Generation (HOG) facility |publisher=Indian Railways}}</ref>\n\n==Technical Specifications==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Technical Specifications<ref name=\"irfca\">{{cite web |url=http://www.irfca.org/faq/faq-loco2e.html#loco |title=Recent Developments |publisher=IRFCA}}</ref>\n|Manufacturers || Chittaranjan Locomotive Works (CLW)<br />Diesel Locomotive Works (DLW)<br />Diesel Locomotive Modernisation Works\n|-\n|Traction Motors || 6FRA 6068 3-phase squirrel-cage induction motors<br />{{convert|850|kW|abbr=on}}, 2180 V, 1283/2484 rpm, 270/310A;<br />Weight-{{convert|2100|kg|abbr=on}}, forced-air ventilation, axle-hung, nose-suspended;<br />Torque {{convert|6330|-|7140|Nm|abbr=on}}<br />~88% efficiency.<!-- Efficiency is P.in/P.out - Six traction motors rated at 850kW each (5100kW input) give 4474kw output - 87.72% efficiency -->\n|-\n|[[Gear Ratio]] || 72:20    , 70:22( for HS Version)\n|-\n|[[Axle load]] || {{convert|20.5|t|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|Wheel diameter || {{convert|1092|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}} new, {{convert|1016|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}} worn\n|-\n|[[Wheelbase]] || {{convert|15700|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|-\n|[[Bogie]]s || [[Co-Co locomotives|Co-Co]], Fabricated [[Flexicoil]] Mark IV [[bogie]]s; bogie wheelbase {{convert|1850|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}} + {{convert|1850|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|-\n|Unsprung mass per axle || {{convert|3.984|t|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|Length over [[Buffer (rail transport)|buffers]] || {{convert|20562|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|-\n|Length over [[Headstock (rolling stock)|headstocks]] || {{convert|19280|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}} \n|-\n|Body width || {{convert|3152|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|-\n|loco weight || {{convert|123|t|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|Cab length || {{convert|2434|mm|in|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|-\n|Pantograph locked down height || {{convert|4255|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|}\n\n==Locomotive Sheds==\n[[File:Yesvantpur bound Express from Tatanagar enters Pithapuram with a WAP7 Locomotive.jpg|alt=|thumb|Lallaguda WAP7]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Zone !! Shed Code !! Name \n!Quantity!! Introduction !! Out of Service !! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |CR || AJNI ||[[Ajni railway station|Ajni]]\n|63|| 27 December 2010 || 1 (WAP-7 #30270 is out of service due to accident damage) || First loco transferred from GZB.Locomotive WAP-7 30543 of this shed named \"OJAS\"\n|-\n|KYN\n|[[Loco Shed, Kalyan|Kalyan]]\n|25\n|21 June 2019\n|\n|First loco transferred from AJNI.used for PushPull Technology.\n|-\n|ER || HWH ||[[Howrah railway station|Howrah]]\n|76|| 20 February 2012 ||  || First loco transferred from GMO; holds the 150th electric locomotive WAP7 37025 of this shed, named \"ASWAMEDH\"\n|-\n| ER || BGA || [[Beliaghata Road railway station]] ||10||\n|-\n|ECR\n|GMO\n|[[Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose Gomoh railway station|Gomoh]]\n|46\n|15 November 2018\n|\n|Recently started Holding WAP7 locos,  serve all routes across [[West Central Railway zone|East Central Railway zone]]. First WAP 7 shed for ECR\n|-\n|NR || GZB ||[[Ghaziabad railway station|Ghaziabad]]\n|152|| 19 May 2000 ||  || First WAP-7 was operated by NR and Indian Railways\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |WCR || TKD ||[[Tughlakabad railway station|Tughlakabad]]\n|87|| 25 January 2013 ||  || First loco transferred from GZB\n\n|-\n| ET ||[[Itarsi Junction railway station|Itarsi]]\n|25|| 1 December 2018 ||  ||Holds 100th DLW WAP7 37073, nicknamed\"SHATAK\".\n|-\n|NCR\n|CNB\n|[[Kanpur Central railway station|Kanpur]]\n|38\n|31 March 2019\n|\n|First loco shed in [[North Central Railway zone]] to hold WAP7 locos\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |SR || RPM ||[[Royapuram railway station|Royapuram]]\n|102|| 21 January 2011 ||  ||First WAP7 locomotive shed of Southern Railway.Holds WAP7 30479, nicknamed\"THANGAM\".\n|-\n| ED ||[[ Electric Loco Shed, Erode|Erode]]\n|37|| 19 October 2017 ||  || First loco transferred from RPM.Holds the WAP7 30573, nicknamed\"CAUVERY\".\n|-\n| SCR || LGD || [[Lallaguda railway station|Lallaguda]] \n|112|| 26 December 2008 ||  ||First WAP7 loco shed for [[South India]] next to [[Ghaziabad, Uttar Pradesh|Ghaziabad.]] 100th WAP-7 Nicknamed \"SHATASHV\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |SER\n|SRC\n|[[Santragachi Junction railway station|Santragachi]]\n|39\n|9 November 2017\n|\n|First loco transferred from GMO\nSER\n|-\n| TATA ||[[Tatanagar Junction railway station|Tatanagar]]\n|38|| 18 April 2017 ||  ||First WAP7 locomotive shed for [[South Eastern Railway zone]].(Located in extreme South eastern of [[Jharkhand]] state).\n|-\n|BNDM\n|[[Bondamunda railway station|Bondamunda]]\n|15\n|31 August 2019\n|\n|First locomotive transferred from [[Tatanagar Junction railway station|Tatanagar]] shed. third WAP-7 shed of [[South Eastern Railway zone]]\n|-\n| SECR || BIA ||[[Bhilai]]\n|54|| 6 September 2012 ||  || First loco transferred from GM